SECTION 5 — Ecotone
The transition zone between ecosystems
5.1 Definition of Ecotone
An ecotone is a transition zone or boundary between two adjacent ecosystems or biotic communities. The
term was coined by F.E. Clements (1905) from the Greek words oikos (house) and tonos (tension/tone). It
is a zone of tension where two ecological communities meet and integrate.
