5.2 Characteristics of Ecotones
• Transitional zone — contains elements of BOTH adjacent communities
• Variable width — can be sharp (cliff edge) or broad (forest-grassland)
• Unique conditions — different microclimate, light, humidity from either community
• Higher species diversity than either adjacent habitat (due to Edge Effect)
• Distinct species — some species are unique to ecotones (edge species)
• Tension zone — competing influences from both adjacent ecosystems
• Dynamic — boundary shifts with seasons and disturbances
• Importance for movement — many animals use ecotones as corridors
