6.2 Why Edge Effect Occurs
• Resource availability — organisms can access resources from BOTH adjacent ecosystems
• Structural diversity — complex physical structure (trees + grasses at forest edge)
• Microhabitat variety — gradients of light, temperature, humidity create many niches
• Reduced competition — generalist species from both ecosystems can coexist
• Edge species — some species are specialised for the ecotone itself
