SECTION 7 — Ecological Habitat
WHERE an organism lives — the physical environment
7.1 Definition of Habitat
A habitat is the physical environment in which an organism lives, grows, and reproduces. It includes all
the abiotic factors (temperature, soil, water, light) and the community of organisms that share that
environment. It is the organism's "address" in nature.
Etymology: From Latin habitare = to dwell/inhabit. A habitat is the "home" of an organism — the place where
it is normally found.
