SECTION 8 — Ecological Niche
The functional role of a species — the most important concept in ecology
8.1 Definition and History
The ecological niche is the functional role and position of a species within an ecosystem —
encompassing all of its interactions with the biotic and abiotic environment. It includes WHAT it eats,
WHERE it lives, WHEN it is active, and HOW it interacts with other species.
Habitat vs Niche — Key Distinction
