4 16. Resource partitioning allows coexistence — reduces niche overlap
4 17. MacArthur's warbler study (1958) — classic spatial niche partitioning
4 18. Character displacement = species diverge MORE where ranges overlap (Brown & Wilson, 1956)
4 19. Biodiversity = genetic + species + ecosystem diversity (E.O. Wilson, 1988)
4 20. Tropical regions have highest species diversity — stable climate, long evolutionary history
